      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 2447: 🟡 **Missing `requestMessageConnection` after successful swarm socket**: The old code called `shared-\u003erequestMessageConnection(uri, deviceId, \"\")` when a swarm socket connected successfully. This line was removed in the refactor, but it served a purpose — ensuring a message channel exists for the peer. If `onNewDeviceConnection` is now the sole path for this, it only fires once on first TCP link establishment; subsequent swarm connections to new conversations with the same peer won\u0027t trigger it again. Verify this is intentional and that the message connection is guaranteed to already exist in all cases.",
