      "message": "Line 340: 🟡 **`connectNode` does not check `isShutdown_`**: Other SwarmManager entry points (e.g., `setKnownNodes`, `maintainBuckets`) check `isShutdown_` before proceeding. `connectNode` does not, which means it can initiate a connection attempt on a shut-down swarm manager.\n\n```suggestion\nvoid\nSwarmManager::connectNode(const NodeId\u0026 nodeId)\n{\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lock(mutex);\n        if (isShutdown_)\n            return;\n        if (isConnectedWith(nodeId))\n            return;\n        addKnownNode(nodeId);\n        if (!routing_table.addConnectingNode(nodeId))\n            return;\n    }\n    tryConnect(nodeId, true);\n}\n```",
